The paper discusses iris recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). However, the paper also focuses on the effects of aging, diseases, and post-mortem changes on iris recognition, which are related to biometrics (cs.BIO) and computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of databases and regression analysis, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
